## §A.6 Bayesian audit deadlines — `2026-09-28` (T-146 days)

n=30 corpus Bayesian model comparison (log Bayes factor ≥ 3 to reject H0
random):

- F-NB-2 (NANOBOT n6 invariant calibration)
- F-RB-2 (RIBOZYME catalytic-core 12-nt calibration)
- F-VIROCAPSID-2 — **RESOLVED cycle 22** (posterior 0.9668 on n=34 corpus,
  log Bayes factor 3.37)

**C0c PASS criterion** (landed 2026-05-06 from §F draft, replaces vague
"closed"):

  PASS ≡ ( log_bf > 3 AND inter-rater κ ≥ 0.6 )
       OR ( honest-negative documented with rubric-normalization preregister )

- **Suspicious-perfect** (log_bf > 50 with single rater) requires κ ≥ 0.6
  across n ≥ 2 independent raters before STRUCTURAL-EXACT promotion. Applies
  to F-RB-2 (log_bf = 79.74 single-rater) → see §G GATE-26-4.
- **Honest-negative** (log_bf < 1) is acceptable closure provided a
  rubric-normalization plan is preregistered for the next cycle stretch.
  Applies to F-NB-2 (log_bf = 0.16) → see §G GATE-26-5.

