## §A.9 Post-closure regression preregister (landed 2026-05-06 from §F draft)

Closes §F UNDEFINED "Post-closure regression falsifiers". One regression
falsifier preregistered per closed C0b falsifier:

- F-TP5-b-REGRESSION
- F-NB-4-REGRESSION
- F-RB-4-REGRESSION
- F-VIROCAPSID-3-REGRESSION

**Trigger**: any merge that touches
`_python_bridge/module/<verb>_*_simulation.py` or `<verb>_calibration.py`.

**PASS criterion** (deterministic, canonical seed):

  (a) PASS-rate identical to closure-cycle baseline;
  (b) all 6/6 deterministic criteria still satisfied;
  (c) registry row hash matches witness baseline.

Wired as CI hook in cycle 26 — see §G GATE-26-6.

**[CI HOOK LANDED 2026-05-06]** `selftest/regression_audit.py` (executable;
stdlib only). Runs all 4 F-*-REGRESSION specs at canonical seed, asserts
PASS sentinel + baseline witness present + baseline essential-fields hash
recorded. Initial run 4/4 PASS:

  F-TP5-b-REGRESSION         PASS  baseline_hash=31f59193aa6359db
  F-NB-4-REGRESSION          PASS  baseline_hash=0cec97b4ab805e2b
  F-RB-4-REGRESSION          PASS  baseline_hash=c0cbc3b428535dc1
  F-VIROCAPSID-3-REGRESSION  PASS  baseline_hash=e350f60a6d59c7ad

CI integration: invoke as pre-merge hook on any PR touching
`_python_bridge/module/<verb>_*_simulation.py` or `<verb>_calibration.py`.
Exit 0 = no regression, exit 1 = regression detected. Full row-by-row
witness diff (cycle 27 stretch) can extend the essential-fields hash
comparison.

